HEADWORD: Polyzonal
<hw>Pol`y*zon"al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Poly-</ets>
+ <ets>zonal</ets>.]</ety> <def>Consisting of many zones or
rings.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Polyzonal lens</b></col> <fld>(Opt.)</fld>, <cd>a lens
made up of pieces arranged zones or rings, -- used in the lanterns of
lighthouses.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Polyzoon</ent>⟦br⟧
